          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How are OTA commission and payment gateway deductions recorded in a hotel's books?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Record the gross room value as revenue and show the platform commission as an expense, instead of booking only the net payout. A Rs 10,000 booking with 18% commission and Rs 200 of gateway charges gives revenue of Rs 10,000, commission expense of Rs 1,800 and a bank receipt of Rs 8,000. Netting off understates turnover for GST."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between an OTA commission deduction and a platform funded discount?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A commission deduction is the platform's fee for the booking and is an expense in the hotel's books, while a platform funded discount is borne by the travel agency and does not reduce the hotel's contracted room rate. Only discounts the hotel itself agrees can reduce taxable value under GST, which makes this a frequent reconciliation error."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is TDS deducted on travel agents?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Commission paid to a travel agent attracts TDS under Section 194H at 2% following the rate cut effective 1 October 2024, once annual commission crosses the threshold. Separately, an online travel agency acting as an e-commerce operator deducts TDS at 0.1% under Section 194-O on the gross booking value before releasing payment to the hotel."
          }
        }
